ordinances and adopting resolutions consistent with this Constitution, in the 
following areas:
i. 

To govern the conduct of the members and other persons within tribal 
jurisdiction;
To promote, protect and provide for the public health, safety and welfare 
of the Tribe and its members; and
To provide by ordinance tribal jurisdiction over Indian Child Welfare 
matters, and other domestic matters;

